Glencore Ltd, a subsidiary of Glencore PLC, has received a subpoena dated 2 July 2018 from the US Department of Justice. The subpoena requires Glencore to produce documents and other records with respect to compliance with the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act and United States money laundering statutes. The requested documents specifically relate to the Glencore Groupâ€™s business in Nigeria, the Democratic Republic of Congo and Venezuela from 2007 to present. Glencore is reviewing the subpoena and will provide further information in due course as appropriate.